gory:George Michael songs]]\n[[Category:The Police songs]]\n[[Category:Songs about prostitutes]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Sting (musician)]]\n", "name_user": "JGabbard", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eWeekly charts:-w", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roxanne_(The_Police_song)"}
{"title_page": "Ana Belen Garcia Antequera", "text_new": "{{short description|Spanish cyclist}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2015}} \n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name          = Ana Belen Garcia Antequera\n| image         =\n| caption       =\n| fullname      =\n| nickname      =\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|1981|1|30|df=yes}}\n| birth_place   = [[Spain]]\n| death_date    =\n| death_place   =\n| height        =\n| weight        =\n| currentteam   =\n| discipline    = [[Road bicycle racing|Road cycling]]\n| role          =\n| ridertype     =\n| amateuryears1 =\n| amateurteam1  =\n| proyears1     = 2007\n| proteam1      = [[Comunidad Valenciana]]\n| proyears2     = 2008\u20132011\n| proteam2      = [[Bizkaia - Durango]]\n| majorwins     =\n}}\n'''Ana Belen Garcia Antequera''' (born 30 January 1981) is a [[Road bicycle racing|road cyclist]] from [[Spain]]. She represented her nation at the [[2006 UCI Road World Championships|2006]], [[2009 UCI Road World Championships|2009]] and [[2010 UCI Road World Championships]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.procyclingstats.com/rider/Ana_Garcia_Antequera|title=Ana Belen Garcia Antequera|accessdate=7 February 2015|work=procyclingstats.com}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.procyclingstats.com/rider/Ana_Garcia_Antequera profile at ''Procyclingstats.com'']\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Garcia Antequera, Ana Belen}}\n[[Category:1981 births]]\n[[Category:Spanish female cyclists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n{{Spain-cycling-bio-1980s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2015}} \n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name          = Ana Belen Garcia Antequera\n| image         =\n| caption       =\n| fullname      =\n| nickname      =\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|1981|1|30|df=yes}}\n| birth_place   = [[Spain]]\n| death_date    =\n| death_place   =\n| height        =\n| weight        =\n| currentteam   =\n| discipline    = [[Road bicycle racing|Road cycling]]\n| role          =\n| ridertype     =\n| amateuryears1 =\n| amateurteam1  =\n| proyears1     = 2007\n| proteam1      = [[Comunidad Valenciana]]\n| proyears2     = 2008\u20132011\n| proteam2      = [[Bizkaia - Durango]]\n| majorwins     =\n}}\n'''Ana Belen Garcia Antequera''' (born 30 January 1981) is a [[Road bicycle racing|road cyclist]] from [[Spain]]. She represented her nation at the [[2006 UCI Road World Championships|2006]], [[2009 UCI Road World Championships|2009]] and [[2010 UCI Road World Championships]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.procyclingstats.com/rider/Ana_Garcia_Antequera|title=Ana Belen Garcia Antequera|accessdate=7 February 2015|work=procyclingstats.com}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.procyclingstats.com/rider/Ana_Garcia_Antequera profile at ''Procyclingstats.com'']\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Garcia Antequera, Ana Belen}}\n[[Category:1981 births]]\n[[Category:Spanish female cyclists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n{{Spain-cycling-bio-1980s-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Lepricavark", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:added short description", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ana_Belen_Garcia_Antequera"}
{"title_page": "Crunchyroll Manga", "text_new": "{{Infobox magazine\n |title           = Crunchyroll Manga\n |image_file      = \n |image_size      = \n |image_caption   = \n |editor          = \n |editor_title    = \n |previous_editor = \n |staff_writer    = \n |frequency       = Weekly\n |circulation     = \n |category        = [[manga]], ''[[Sh\u014dnen manga|sh\u014dnen]]''\n |company         = [[Crunchyroll]]\n |publisher       = \n |firstdate       = {{start date and age|2013|10|30}}\n |finaldate       = \n |based           = [[San Francisco, California|San Francisco]], [[California]], United States\n |country         = Worldwide (except China, France, Italy, Japan and Germany)\n |language        = English\n |website         = \n |issn            = \n}}\n'''''Crunchyroll Manga''''' is a [[online magazine|digital]] ''[[sh\u014dnen manga|sh\u014dnen]]'' [[manga]] anthology published by [[Crunchyroll]] in North America. It began distribution on October 30, 2013. The service launched with a lineup of twelve titles, with chapters released simultaneously with their Japanese release. ''Crunchyroll Manga'' provides English speaking readers with officially licensed editions of the latest installments of popular manga published by [[Futabasha]], [[Kodansha]], [[Kadokawa Shoten]] and [[Sh\u014dnen Gah\u014dsha]] soon after their release in Japan.\n\n==History==\nOn October 26, 2013, [[Crunchyroll]] confirmed that the ''Crunchyroll Manga'' service would be released October 30, 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2013-10-26/crunchyroll-to-simultaneously-offer-kodansha-manga-in-170-countries|title=Crunchyroll to Simultaneously Offer Kodansha Manga in 170 Countries|date=October 26, 2013|publisher=Anime News Network|accessdate=October 26, 2013}}</ref> The service will be available in 170 countries, with the exception of Japan, China, France, Germany and Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nikkei.com/article/DGXNASFE2600M_W3A021C1MM8000/|script-title=ja:\u4eba\u6c17\u6f2b\u753b\u3001\u96fb\u5b50\u66f8\u7c4d\u3067170\u30ab\u56fd\u306b\u5373\u6642\u914d\u4fe1\u3000\u8b1b\u8ac7\u793e|language=Japanese|work=Nikkei|date=October 26, 2013|accessdate=October 26, 2013}}</ref>\n\nOn February 17, 2018, [[Crunchyroll]] announced that [[Kodansha]] titles excluding ''[[Fairy Tail]]'' would be removed from the manga section of the site on March 1. The titles are still available for purchase as eBooks.<ref name=\"Kodansha\">{{cite web|title=Crunchyroll Manga to No Longer Offer Catalog Chapters of Kodansha Titles|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-02-16/crunchyroll-manga-to-no-longer-offer-catalog-chapters-of-kodansha-titles/.127906|website=Anime News Network|accessdate=March 1, 2018|date=February 17, 2018}}</ref> On March 1, 2018, [[Crunchyroll]] announced that they would simultaneously publish new Kodansha manga titles as they release in Japan.<ref>{{cite web|title=New Crunchyroll Manga Simulpubs Starting March 2018!|url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/forumtopic-1014753/new-crunchyroll-manga-simulpubs-starting-march-2018?referrer=editorial_cr_news_manga|website=Crunchyroll Forums|accessdate=March 1, 2018|date=March 1, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Features==\nManga chapters are available to read online through the website or on web-enabled devices through Crunchyroll or an official app. Readers can sign up for an All-Access or Manga subscription for full access to several manga titles. Anime and Drama subscribers can read only the latest chapters with limited advertisements.<ref name=\"CRM\">{{cite web|url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2013/10/30/its-here-crunchyroll-manga-is-now-open|title=It's Here! Crunchyroll Manga is Now Open!|last=Macias|first=Patrick|date=October 30, 2013|accessdate=October 30, 2013}}</ref>\n\nThe format of the anthology generally mirrors that of the equivalent magazine issues, typically featuring the same cover illustrations, as well as color interior pages. If a physical copy or digital copy of a series is available for sale, it might not be available on ''Crunchyroll Manga''.<ref name=\"CRM\"/>\n\n==Full series==\n===Ongoing series===\nSeries that are still currently running in Crunchyroll Manga.\n{{Serialization list/header\n| Completed   = No}}\n{{Serialization list\n| Ongoing   = yes\n| Title     = [[Crayon Shin-chan#Manga|Crayon Shin-chan]]\n| KanjiTitle=\n| Author    =  {{sortname|Yoshito|Usui}}\n| Genre     = [[Comedy]]\n| First     = \n| FirstRef    = \n| Last      =\n}}\n{{Serialization list\n| Ongoing   = yes\n| Title     = [[APOSIMZ]]\n| KanjiTitle= ([[Monthly Sh\u014dnen Sirius]])\n| Author    =  {{sortname|Tsutomu|Nihei}}\n| Genre     = [[Action fiction|Action]], [[Drama]], [[Science fiction]]\n| First     = March 1, 2018\n| FirstRef    = \n| Last      =\n}}\n{{Serialization list\n| Ongoing   = yes\n| Title     = [[Arpeggio of Blue Steel]]\n| KanjiTitle= ([[Young King OURs]])\n| Author    =  {{sortname|Ark|Performance|nolink=1}}\n| Genre     = [[Adventure fiction|Adventure]], [[Drama]], [[Military science fiction]], [[Romance manga|Romance]]\n| First     = January 29, 2014\n| FirstRef    = <br />(Chapter #53)\n| Last      =\n}}\n{{Serialization list\n| Ongoing   = yes\n| Title     = [[Drifting Dragons]]\n| KanjiTitle= ([[good! Afternoon]])\n| Author    =  {{sortname|Taku|Kuwabara|nolink=1}}\n| Genre     = [[Action fiction|Action]], [[Adventure fiction|Adventure]], [[Comedy]], [[Drama]], [[Fantasy]]\n| First     = March 1, 2018\n| FirstRef    = <br />\n| Last      =\n}}\n{{Serialization list\n| Ongoing   = yes\n| Title     = [[Farewell, My Dear Cramer]]\n| KanjiTitle= ([[Monthly Sh\u014dnen Magazine]])\n| Author    =  {{sortname|Naoshi|Arakawa|nolink=1}}\n| Genre     = [[Drama]], [[Sports]] ([[Association football]])\n| First     = March 1, 2018\n| FirstRef    = <br />\n| Last      =\n}}\n{{Serialization list\n| Ongoing   = yes\n| Title     = [[Grand Blue|Grand Blue Dreaming]]\n| KanjiTitle= ([[good! Afternoon]])\n| Author    =  {{sortname|Kenji|Inoue|nolink=1}}\n| Genre     = [[Comedy]], [[Drama]], [[Romance manga|Romance]], [[Sports]] ([[Diving]])\n| First     = March 1, 2018\n| FirstRef    = <br />\n| Last      =\n}}\n{{Serialization list\n| Ongoing   = yes\n| Title     = [[Kiznaiver]]\n| KanjiTitle= ([[Dengeki Maoh]])\n| Author    =  {{sortname|Roji|Karegishi|nolink=1}}\n| Genre     = [[Drama]], [[Science fiction]]\n| First     = March 25, 2016\n| FirstRef    = <br />(Chapter #0)\n| Last      =\n}}\n{{Serialization list\n| Ongoing   = yes\n| Title     = [[Our Precious Conversations]]\n| KanjiTitle= ([[Dessert (magazine)|Dessert]])\n| Author    =  Robico\n| Genre     = [[Comedy]], [[Romance manga|Romance]]\n| First     = March 1, 2018\n| FirstRef    = <br />\n| Last      =\n}}\n{{Serialization list\n| Ongoing   = yes\n| Title     = ReCollection\n| KanjiTitle= (Monthly Action)\n| Author    =  {{sortname|Ichigo|Takano|nolink=1}}\n| Genre     = [[List of romance manga|Romance]], [[slice of life]]\n| First     = January 24, 2014\n| FirstRef    = <br />(Chapter #3)\n| Last      =\n}}\n{{Serialization list\n| Ongoing   = yes\n| Title     = [[To Your Eternity]]\n| KanjiTitle= ([[Weekly Sh\u014dnen Magazine]])\n| Author    =  {{sortname|Yoshitoki|Oima|nolink=1}}\n| Genre     = [[Adventure fiction|Adventure]], [[Drama]], [[Fantasy]], [[Romance manga|Romance]]\n| First     = March 1, 2018\n| FirstRef    = <br />\n| Last      =\n}}\n{{Serialization list\n| Ongoing   = yes\n| Title     = [[Toppu GP]]\n| KanjiTitle= ([[Afternoon (magazine)|Afternoon]])\n| Author    =  {{sortname|Kosuke|Fujishima}}\n| Genre     = [[Drama]], [[Sports]]\n| First     = March 1, 2018\n| FirstRef    = <br />\n| Last      =\n}}\n{{Serialization list\n| Ongoing   = yes\n| Title     = [[Wave, Listen to Me!]]\n| KanjiTitle= ([[Afternoon (magazine)|Afternoon]])\n| Author    =  {{sortname|Hiroaki|Samura}}\n| Genre     = [[Comedy]], [[Drama]], [[Slice of life]]\n| First     = March 1, 2018\n| FirstRef    = <br />\n| Last      =\n}}\n{{Serializat